<br>
Here I was, surfing the web boards. Low and behold, I see an ally of our guild has posted, and they invite us to a raid on CoM. <br>
<br>
So, I run there and camp out, to play an alt till the raid time. I find a few people in the zone putting a raid together, and I am asked to join. What they hey, why not - betters my chance of getting me an ORS.<br>
<br>
<br>
The raid starts off good, and I actually was feeling useful. I made the KS group, everyone wanted a piece of my focus items, Vonn is negotiating with extreme prejudice - all is well.  <br>
<br>
There were 12 of us, mostly 55+. Turns out we really kicked some ass! We could even handle 4 black reavers at a time, with minimal losses! So good we run through the place in little under and hour and a half, killing everything in the process.<br>
<br>
When we finally get to neh' ashiir, I decide to check my odds on the ORS.<br>
<br>
/who  wizard<br>
<br>
There are no players in everquest who match those filters.<br>
<br>
/who  Necro<br>
<br>
There are no players in everquest who match those filters.<br>
<br>
/who  Magi<br>
<br>
Me- 51 magician.<br>
<br>
/who  enchanter<br>
Some level 60 enchanter.<br>
<br>
So, I go check the chanter out. Epicd and has ORS equipped.<br>
<br>
Woot! I am the only one on the raid who CAWU the shield!<br>
<br>
We pull neh, take him down fairly quickly. What do you know, the ORS dropped! I was ecstatic! The shield was going to default to me!<br>
The raid leader asks who wants in on the roll, and of course I respond.<br>
<br>
THEN - the unspeakable happens. Some epicd level 60 ranger in NOTV crap steps out of the shadows of hell and wines till he gets in on the roll so he can twink one of his damn alts!<br>
<br>
Raidleader shouts :  Chadly 1 , Ranger 2.<br>
<br>
Raidleader rolls magic Dice. <br>
It could have been any number from 1 to 2, but this time it turned up to be 2.<br>
<br>
DAMNIT DAMNIT DAMNIT DAMNIT, burn in hell rangers. I hate you. I hate pick up raids. <br>
<br>
<br>
